title: Grateful Dead Live at Market Square Arena on 1981-12-05
lineage: MAC > Nakamichi CR-5A > Edirol FA-66 > Wavelab 2448 > CD-Wave (24bit output) > R8Brain > TLH > FLAC 1644 tagged. Transfer by Andrew F. 08/2017
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Friend Of The Devil-> CC Rider, Cumberland Blues-> El Paso, Ramble On Rose, Passenger, Bird Song-> Let It Grow

Set 2

Shakedown Street > Lost Sailor > Saint of Circumstance, Big Railroad Blues > Playing in the Band > Drums > Space > The Wheel > Playing in the Band > Stella Blue > Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text:
Outstanding You are very good at finding that perfect spot to tape. This is another one of your OUTSTANDING recordings. 
 Am only half way threw 1st set and this one is dialed in . can hear everyone.

THE Show of Shows !!! If there was one spot to be on planet earth on December 5, 1981, it was standing on the Market Square Arena floor in Indianapolis, Indiana seventy feet in front of the Boyz.  This show rivals 8/19/80, 9/2/80, and 2/27/81 for me.  And of the four, now there is only one Holy Grail of solid F.O.B. recordings left for my library.  And that's 8/19/80 - because this F.O.B. is KILLER!  And I've only been waiting for it from the moment I walked out the arena doors thirty-six years ago. Thank you, thank you, thank you Craig, Mr. Stan, and Mr. Vernon.  

The fact that only 324 views of this show have materialized since September is a damn shame because it is an absolute MUST HAVE for every collection.  As I've declared in the other reviews, this is the wildest, most intense show I ever saw.  They blew me right out of my socks.  Five big stars for this manic, X-Factor blowout!
